The need for speed The Run competes across America.
Revision
Originally a race without problem is transformed because of a set of stupid mistakes of people who have nothing to do in a routine morning commute to work.
It fulfills everyone’s ambition to a certain extent, but it’s useless if no one wants to do anything more.
The new subtitled part The Run produced high expectations before its release.
It promised to take a new direction with the already old Need for Speed racing series and to release a kind of game from the playable games that would not be counted with just points.
So we were curious about how the added passages will be in which the main hero gets out of his car and does what he wants.
As it is already done in the NFS series, the result is completely different from what we expected.
These are potentially arcade racing games but the whole thing pulls down because of a few unnecessary mistakes that have already existed for several years.
These are not really mistakes but rather the expression of incomprehensible laziness on the part of developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are caught in the adventure whose main hero Jack has characteristic problems and to fix them starts to participate in illegal races throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast in San Francisco and your mission is to arrive first in New York.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages and then into more than 50 races.
As a result, each race is done on another route and the stages planned in different environments that stand out from each other quite well and are interesting.
The player does not feel for a single moment that the game offers him something identical.
Some environments are also pretty nice even if the graphical technical level is the same as the previous series.
This is not the end of the world.
But driving through the desert, in autumn landscapes or in highly snowy mountains is very visually pleasing.
The tests are also occasionally decorated with an atypical element.
For example, in the desert you find yourself in a sandstorm that significantly reduces your visibility.
Then in the mountains you have to be careful that an avalanche does not fall on you.
Besides that, the different races are well arranged one after the other.
There are only a few, but that is enough.
There are moments you strive to exceed the required number of opponents (as in a classic race) then you will race against the watch (classic duel with the chronometer) and then again you are waiting for another duel with an opponent.
From time to time you also have the police entering the game and trying to make the situation difficult.
The novelty is the off-vehicle passages.
Rather, it’s an interactive animation when Jack mostly runs away in front of someone and you have to help him by tapping the right button at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
What is surprising is that there are fewer times of this type than you expect (to be specific there are only three).
As a result, it is like this because this element is not likely to interfere and is placed, in the context described above, in the elements that embellish the game.
The driving pattern is in the tradition of the previous games.
Which means that at the moment there is nothing extraordinary but it cannot be said to be negative.
When it comes to realistic simulation, you’ll need to look elsewhere.
But although we can find better in the competition the driving model goes very well with the type of design of the races.
So everything is okay.
Problems begin to appear after a while.
In contrast to the model of driving, that of collisions is not yet at the point.
We don't expect complicated deformation and collisions from this game, but when you don't have, during a collision with any object, the slightest idea of how your car behaves, so it's not completely good.
During tight overtaking you sometimes touch each other slightly but otherwise your self goes into crazy volts.
Or it is in crumbs.
Thanks to the reboot system this is not really a problem but it really annoys you.
The restart is done in such a way that when you have broken the figure or you have gone out into the setting the game brings you back to the last point on the route.
But you only have 5 restarts.
When you have used the 5 restarts you have to start the game again from the beginning.
So it's more of a tool, in case something doesn't go right, than something you can really count on.
Sometimes the restarts do not help and you have to find the solution by remembering from memory the piece of route in question.
The great thing about this game is that the same actions are in the same places.
For example, there are certain corners that you have to pass in a certain way or else it does not happen.
Otherwise, you will encounter "civilian" vehicles in the same configuration as if you were arriving first, fifth, 5 seconds early or one minute late.
What makes you angry is the situations when you see the opponent easily pass between two cars coming in the opposite direction and when you arrive, you have to either stand aside and circumvent them or brake them.
It doesn’t matter if you go in front of it because it is “calculated” in such a way that for the given situation it always happens very close to your nose.
Opponents have other advantages.
Throughout the game, you arrive in certain places, again without worrying about the weather, and you always have the same opponent ahead of you in the same place.
This irritates the most at the end of the game when you ride on a long deck in the opposite direction.
The opponent must pass in front of you at all costs.
When it passes you it hides the view of the other vehicles in the opposite direction and you collide a good many times.
It can be understood that the goal of this game is to do something exciting and full of adrenaline, but it is clear that you get bored quickly.
And that’s a shame because through a simple driving pattern the game is interesting and the places with so much action that you don’t have time to follow everything that happens.
And it doesn’t matter if it’s because of the concept of 50 unique itineraries, that the order of the races is such that there’s no chance of getting bored or anything else.
The original idea is the change of car during the races.
You have to pay attention to the petrol pumps on the routes as you can change cars but most of the time the one you have is enough for you.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are ideal for cities, large American cylinders for straight highways and super exotic sports cars on very technical drives for example on lacing roads in the mountains.
And the challenge mode, which are racing in particular places that you know of adventure, goes very well with the main regime of the story.
You receive not only medals but also experience points that add to your profile that is common to challenges and adventure.
When you have reached the highest level of driver, different objects begin to unlock:
It connects online with Autolog, which compares your results with those of other players and gives you other functions in the community.
One of the most difficult moves to understand is the situation of the last race of the adventure.
You arrive with your car in the subway tunnel (it looks like) where you ride in the dark on the tracks (it looks like).
Your speed indicator tells you between 150 and 200 km/h (in advance) and behind you comes a subway train that sends you the car directly to the scrap.
At the writing we had a discussion for a few days about whether someone really thought when creating this game or whether the authors really take us for fools.
The technical part of the game is not extra, but the visual part is as a rule nice and in some cases really great.
What is embarrassing is that in more extreme situations, the imagery does not hold up and in some cases tragically.
This is especially true for accidents with a large number of participants when fluid imaging is no longer of any use to you.
The sound part is good and the track is your choice.
In order to please as many people and especially the youngest audience a new soundtrack was created in the style of "I mix everything", but one can expect that no one will buy the game for the music.
Overall impression of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore really confusing.
If the game didn’t have these stupid mistakes we could say without fear that this is the best NFS production in recent years.
But this game feels like it’s not over.
The fun is really good but be prepared for the mistakes to hit you in the eyes with the force of an aerodrome reflector.
The Velvet Students in concert with the choirs of Charles University
The Festa Academica festival offers for the third time festivities that connect International Student Day with the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical part.
During the festival there are 20 choirs from higher and secondary schools.
The highlight of the festival is two concerts organized on November 17.
“Charles University has an important part in this festival.”
"Among the choirs is the Choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and Humanities, in the committee of the festival sits the rector Vaclav Hampl", says the head of the organizing team Jakub Calou.
The highlight of the festival is the Choir of High Schools and Secondary Classes concert which takes place with free admission on November 17th from 2 p.m. on the space located in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
On the program is the composition of the well-known Czech jazzman Karel Ruzicka, Celebration Jazz mass.
In the evening there is the concert "Students of velvet" in the premises of the National House in Vinohrady in which the choirs of the higher schools as well as that of Charles University perform.
The aim of the Festival Academica is not only to celebrate International Student Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the velvet revolution, but also to present choir music of the highest level to the public and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Hearts Union in cooperation with the Jan Kepler High School.
All the action is under the aegis of Bohuslav Svoboda, Mayor of Prague and Vaclav Hampl, Rector of Charles University.
The festival takes place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
The program also offers high-level concerts, music encounters, student happening and other activities.
Interested parties will find all the information on the web pages of the festival www.festaacademica.cz.
Vicenova, Ambassador to the European Union:
Czechs behave like negativists and eurosceptics
"The Lisbon Treaty has radically removed the balance between the institutions"
“I didn’t expect such a hard war.”
"It will last 5.6 years before the situation calms down and all players get used to their new role," said Milena Vicenova, the Czech ambassador to the European Union, in a statement.
When she managed to describe the different EU bodies and their relationships in such a comprehensible and visible way, to the point that a large number of lecturers from Charles University’s Faculty of Law could envy her, she showed how much she takes her motto “understandably and openly about Europe” very seriously.
Ms Vicenova paid tribute to the work of Herman Van Rompuye, the new Permanent President of the European Council.
“From the beginning, there was criticism that he is ugly, that he is a leather-rounder, that he cannot fulfill any mission and I have to say that he has taken everyone’s breath away because he plays his role to perfection.”
“He is a man who knows how to listen to 27 member states, how to communicate well with them and has a clear vision of the direction Europe needs to take.”
She explained the new position of the High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Defence Policy as part of an answer to the question: "Who is who in the European Union?" "What phone number should I call?", thus as an important step towards the uniqueness and greater legibility of the Union's policy vis-à-vis states, such as China or India.
No one wants to ban us from our syrecky (cooked cheese that smells very strong)
Mrs Vicenova also mentioned the agenda that the European Council has lived, lives and will live in the near future.
She called the Czech Presidency a success two years ago.
The Czechs solved the looming financial crisis, the gas crisis or organized a Summit for an Eastern Partnership.
She called the government’s downfall very negative and damaged the Czech Republic’s image.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, "the activity has been in full swing" not only for the Presidency but also for the financial crisis that continues to be resolved even now.
In addition, we must approve the new Union septimal budget, which is becoming very complicated due to the current economic situation.
As it seems that the budget will be thin and with a view to saving, which branch will take priority, which countries will be helped the most, at least, everything is to be resolved in the context of future negotiations.
The Ambassador recalled her slogans with which she arrived in Brussels "For an understandable Europe".
“I really don’t like abbreviations, foreign words, jargon that nobody understands.
As the citizen must understand, it is true that in Brussels no one makes round or twisted pickles, bananas that are different sizes or that no one has forbidden us to make syrecky.
She wants to make better use of the EU environment and see more Czechs in the EU institutions.
A multi-speed Europe awaits us
According to the Ambassador, Czechs have a reputation for being eurosceptics and people who only see things in their negative aspects more than positively.
Moreover, she is sorry to see such a small Czech representation in the European institutions.
She believes that the fault is the result of several factors, such as the shyness of our candidates, their inability to write a cover letter and the lack of support from the Czech side.
In addition to a successful Czech presidency, she then underlined the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Group.
"Believe me, when the Polish, the Magyar, the Slovak come to me, this Frenchman says to me, 'Hey, what are you doing there, what is this Visegrad group still doing?' and he's not at all happy."
According to Vicenova, in the near future, tough new fiscal policy rules are awaiting member countries.
It is the concept of a two-speed, if not multi-speed Europe that prevails rather than a "new European Federation".
“We have countries in the eurozone and countries outside the eurozone.”
“We have the Schengen area, we also have the institute of enhanced cooperation.”
In the first place it was said that the countries that want to cooperate with each other and those that don’t want to stay in their corner.”
“There will be a lot of institutes of this kind and there will be a truly two-speed Europe,” Vicenova said.
From this point of view, she also appreciated the mission of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuye to determine the basis according to which all the themes having an impact on the EU should be discussed among all EU members and not only the members of the eurozone.
History of a brand:
The IBM innovator begins the second century of its existence
If someone were to look for the word that most closely expresses the IBM strategy, the closest one would be “the long term.”
For a wide audience IBM is the symbol of the technological revolution, is a firm felt as very current and yet since its creation it has been a hundred years.
The basis for this long-term strategy was laid by the firm’s first chief executive, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He left this slogan that a large number of global problems can be solved as long as people are willing to think.
His slogan "THINK!" became the imprint around which the life of a future giant will develop (and also the title of the internal magazine that IBM began publishing in 1935).
It was the foundation of Watson’s carefully crafted corporate culture.
For us, IBM means long-term thinking of continuous forward-looking movements.
IBM survived a hundred years thanks to the fact that it always remained true to its core values and yet was not afraid to change all the others around it.
This allowed us in our first century to transform technology, business and society.
We hope that in the second century we will reach even more," said the current director of the firm Samuel J. Palmisano.
A well-prepared system
Watson, in the 1930s, began caring for his employees like Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM people were the only American employees to have paid for vacations, insurance paid by the employer plus an elegant employee uniform and a well-crafted system of rewards for inventors and merchants.
Similarly, IBM has a well-designed customer relationship system.
The company was at first brilliant at discovering talent – as one of the first firms to have abolished all forms of discrimination and thus had a choice.
The current plan is completely in the spirit of the anti-discrimination strategy since it will be a woman – Virginia Rometty – who should replace Palmisano at the head of IBM.
She has worked at IBM for 30 years and is currently Head of Sales, Marketing and Strategy.
Over the past few years, IBM has been doing what we call jamy, online brainstorming, from which a lot of future strategies and innovations have come.
No wonder he has a lot of ideas - in the firm there are almost 500,000 people working.
