So was the work of the person of Cali who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A Cali typist went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is crucial.
Last November 4th, a typist of the Cali ITC went down in history as the person who confirmed the identity of the supreme leader of the FARC: "Alfonso Cano", by confronting his fingerprints.
Of the seven typists working in the ITC’s local offices, this week was the turn of “availability” of Eliazar González, a Puerto Tejada man who has been working in the field of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in the municipalities of Chocó, where many times he had to spend more than five days in the forest to get to the place where the corpses were to be identified.
In the year 2000 he was transferred to the capital of Valle and after taking appropriate courses he specialized in typography, which is the study of friction skin, i.e. palms and feet.
During the week of the operation against the alias Alfonso Cano Eliazar was warned to take clothes with him for at least three days.
Something very big was waiting for him.
Friday night he left for Cauca in a helicopter from Palmyra.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected to be the man who ran the oldest guerrilla in the world, so he was asked to carry the card with the ten fingerprints of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
But when he arrived with the investigative team at the location of the corpse, he did not recognize it by its physical appearance, as it was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He didn’t have a beard, he was dressed like a local farmer, without glasses and much leaner.
But the fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a picker and a lantern, Eliazar compared the corpse’s fingerprints with those of the map.
His eye did not deceive him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was the official who confirmed to Defense Minister Juan Carlos Pinzón that yes, he was the supreme leader of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a typist from Sijín de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos gave Eliazar González, in a press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don’t know about our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, with no margin for error, that can be crucial in solving crimes.
In addition to identifying the corpses, typists support investigations into crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of those captured.
When captured, many offenders present fake ID cards or do not have documents.
We take their fingerprints and look for them in the database.
The researcher said that in a case of theft he had to remove part of the wall of a house, because in this place the thief had pressed his hand to bring out a safe full of jewelry and money.
“The walls are difficult because they are not adequate surfaces to get a fingerprint, but in this case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender who had participated in different robberies,” he recalls.
Fingerprints can also dispel or confirm suspects in homicide cases.
Recently we found a dead man, with bottles of drink around him.
Through the investigation it was determined that a relative may be a suspect in the crime and indeed a fingerprint on the bottle coincided.
Even if it doesn't guarantee that he's the killer, it puts him on the scene.
A CTI typist explained that we extract "fingerprints of objects with chemical or physical reagents".
When they appear, a picker or strip is used to pick them up.
Subsequently, the fingerprints are sent to Asif, the database of deductants, or to the National Civil Registry.
“The problem is that there are still a lot of Colombians without papers,” said the ITC expert.
He explained that not everything is how it is shown in the CSI television program.
As everything that shines is not gold, everything that one touches does not necessarily become a footprint.
However, it can be used if the necessary confrontation is made.
