The future head of the Italian government, Mario Monti, has called for some time for the markets to form his team and implement a program, which will contain “sacrifices”, in order to recover the credibility lost in the last months of the Berlusconi government.
The former European Commissioner was in discussions with political parties yesterday before meeting with trade unions and employers today.
It should set up a relatively small cabinet of technocrats outside Parliament.
